
Overview of verb evaporate

The verb evaporate has 4 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (2) evaporate, vaporize, vaporise -- (lose or cause to lose liquid by vaporization leaving a more concentrated residue; "evaporate milk")
2. evaporate, vaporise -- (cause to change into a vapor; "The chemist evaporated the water")
3. evaporate, vaporise -- (change into a vapor; "The water evaporated in front of our eyes")
4. melt, disappear, evaporate -- (become less intense and fade away gradually; "her resistance melted under his charm"; "her hopes evaporated after years of waiting for her fiance")
